One of the speakers at the festival yesterday talked about the possibility that China might

29:35.760 --> 29:42.560
try and invade Taiwan. He suggested that militarily that could probably be defended,

29:42.560 --> 29:47.760
but the consequence would be that China might unleash a cyber war on the west

29:47.760 --> 29:55.440
that we couldn't defend against. Does that technological war worry you? Is that on your list

29:55.440 --> 30:03.360
of things that are challenging humanity along with nuclear power and climate change and ordinary

30:03.360 --> 30:12.480
war and so on? Well, we have to bear in mind that the world's major propaganda system in the United

30:12.480 --> 30:21.520
States, which also has an enormous effect on Britain, largely the satellite of the United

30:21.600 --> 30:30.400
States by now, one of its main themes is you have to hate China, critical, yellow peril,

30:31.200 --> 30:36.960
so we have to be very worried about China invading Taiwan. Is there any sign of that?

30:39.440 --> 30:45.680
There's some good point to build up of military in the area, exercises that are going very close

30:45.680 --> 30:56.640
to airspace. Military exercises largely in response to US provocation. So when there is

30:57.440 --> 31:06.880
a policy called the One China Policy, it's been in place for 50 years, was settled in the 1970s.

31:06.880 --> 31:16.880
The policy is US and China agree that Taiwan is part of China and both agree to what was called

31:16.880 --> 31:26.320
strategic ambiguity. We don't say it in words, but we agree that we will do nothing to disrupt

31:27.120 --> 31:38.000
this program by threats to challenging. Who's been challenging it? China's not a saintly power,

31:38.000 --> 31:45.680
there's plenty you can preserve. But in reality, in this case, it's the US that's been provoking it,

31:45.760 --> 31:56.800
partly just militarily. The official US policy is quoting it to encircle China

31:57.520 --> 32:06.960
with a ring of sentinel states with advanced weapons, advanced precision weapons aimed at China,

32:07.920 --> 32:24.240
South Korea, Taiwan, Japan, Guam, Australia, all surrounding China to encircle and constrain it.

32:25.280 --> 32:33.040
In the case of Taiwan, the US has been regularly breaking the strategic ambiguity.

32:33.760 --> 32:42.480
So when House Speaker Nancy Pelosi went to Taiwan, that was saying we're breaking the

32:42.480 --> 32:51.760
arrangements. China did respond, as you described, with naval maneuvers, to indicate that it can,

32:51.760 --> 33:00.240
